$ /var/db/repos/gentoo/profiles/license_group

`/var/db/repos/gentoo/profiles/license_group` stores license groups.

A *license group* is the first entry of a line where all characters are capital letters. The entries on the line following the license group are the individual licenses:
code {
GROUPNAME LICENSEONE LICENSETWO …
code }

sa:

  In the `ACCEPT_LICENSE` value of `→ Linux/fhs/etc/portage/make_conf`, a license group is identified by the at sign `@`.

  Licenses are stored in the directory `→ Linux/fhs/var/db/repos/gentoo/licenses`.

